paragraphs.title: Average prices grouped by the num. of people that can accommodate
paragraphs.text:
%sql
WITH subquery AS(
 SELECT AVG(price) PRICE, district, beds, COUNT(1) AS cnt
    FROM airbnb
    WHERE beds <= ${max_accommodations=4}
     AND price < 1000
    GROUP BY district, beds
)
SELECT * 
FROM subquery q2
INNER JOIN (
    SELECT DISTINCT(district)
    FROM subquery q1
    WHERE q1.cnt > ${min_count_of_listings=50}
) AS distinct_neigh
ON distinct_neigh.district = q2.district
WHERE cnt > 15

paragraphs.title: Review Ratings Compared to the Number of Reviews
paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT review_scores_rating, number_of_reviews
FROM airbnb
WHERE review_scores_rating > "${min_review_score=0}"

paragraphs.title: Review Score Rating Compared to the Price
paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT review_scores_rating, price
FROM airbnb
WHERE review_scores_rating > "${min_review_score=0}"
    AND price < "${price_max=1000}"

paragraphs.title: Availability Distribution Compared to the Price
paragraphs.text:
%sql
SELECT availability_365, price
FROM airbnb
WHERE availability_365 > "${min_availability=0}"
    AND price < "${price_max=1000}"
